# CI Documentation

The canonical CI reference is **[`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md)**.

## Required on every CI change

When editing workflows, composite actions, CI scripts, or `docker/ci/Dockerfile`, **update `scripts/ci/README.md` in the same PR** if any of these change:

- Workflow triggers, job names, or job ordering
- Path filters (`changes` outputs) or skip conditions
- Caches, artifacts, or container images used
- Entry scripts (`run-pr-*.sh`, `verify-*.sh`)
- Reusable workflow inputs/outputs
- Local verify commands (`npm run ci:verify*`)

## Also check

- [`.cursor/rules/ci-workflow-triggers.mdc`](ci-workflow-triggers.mdc) — short agent summary; keep aligned with README
- [`.cursor/rules/ci-validation.mdc`](ci-validation.mdc) — cross-pipeline validation rules
- [`scripts/RELEASE.md`](../../scripts/RELEASE.md) — only if release/publish flow changes
- Root [`README.md`](../../README.md) — only if user-facing `ci:verify` commands change

## Do not

- Document CI only in cursor rules without updating `scripts/ci/README.md`
- Leave stale job names (e.g. old `build-pr` / `quality` split) in docs after refactors
